{
  "stem": "7506.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He'd either take me on his bicycle, which is, of course, very typical in Holland.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Still is today.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when I was a little bit bigger, he bought me a secondhand bicycle, which he-- they had to elevate the pedals so that my feet could reach the pedals, because at that time, my legs weren't long enough.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they couldn't lower the saddle of the bicycle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my sister never did go fishing with me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She stayed more with my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was more-- as I look upon it now, so many years after the event, it's like it was more a boys' thing to do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't a thing where girls would be included.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's name in English is Cissie, spelled C-I-S-S-I-E.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But in Dutch, it is Sientje, which is an old fashioned Dutch name, also used in the diminutive for the name Sien.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her name in Dutch is spelled S-I-E-N-T-J-E.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother was not working, only looking after the family, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[COUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly games like hide and seek, things like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or when we would get a little bit older, skipping with a rope.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or a game which I don't know the name of today, where you with chalk make marks on the-- on the pavement and you kind of-- I don't know what it's called, hop, skip, and jump, or something like that.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I remember-- I remember that kind of game.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- my-- my grandfather would make the kiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we'd all sit around.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my grandmother would have baked her own bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I always remember, one of the things I remember so well about my father's mother, my grandmother, that she used to cut the bread holding it against her bosom, cutting it like that.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
